Virginia Tech, a renowned technical and applied studies institution, was founded in 1872 as a land-grant school.
It is a hub for research in biotechnology, energy, and fuel-cell technology.
The campus was struck by a tragic shooting incident, resulting in the deaths of 32 individuals.
President George W. Bush attended a memorial service to honor the victims.
The university community and the nation mourned the senseless loss.
Classes were canceled for the week as the campus grappled with the aftermath of the deadliest school shooting in U.S. history.
